Greek Bond Buyback Would Cut Debt by $28 Billion, Spiegel Says

-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 
2011-07-16T16:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-16/greek-bond-buyback-would-cut-debt-by-28-billion-spiegel-says.html
A Greek bond buyback financed by the
European Financial Stability Facility could help reduce the
country’s debt by 20 billion euros ($28 billion),  Der Spiegel 
reported, citing calculations by the German Finance Ministry.  The buyback is “one of a number of alternatives” that are
being tested on behalf of Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble ,
the magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Suess in Frankfurt at 
